<br>
What I've got:<br>
Cost - Ability<br>
3 - Run 3<br>
3 - Improved Stamina 3<br>
12 - Improved Natural Durability 3<br>
<br>
Then:<br>
5 - AOE Taunt <br>
5 - Physical Enhancement<br>
12 - Combat Agility 3<br>
12 - Combat Stability 3<br>
10 - Planar Power 5<br>
<br>
At this point, diminishing returns look to be setting in for the HP and damage avoidance AAs, so next up:<br>
12 - Stalwart Endurance 3 <br>
<br>
Then back to spending truly stunning amounts of AA on defense:<br>
30 - Innate Defense 5<br>
30 - Lightning Reflexes 5<br>
9 - Planar Durability<br>
<br>
All of the defensive side maxxed out, its now time to work on offense:<br>
12 - Combat Fury 3<br>
9 - Ambidexterity <br>
18 - Flurry 3<br>
9 - Ferocity 3<br>
9 - Fury of the Ages 3<br>
18 - Punishing Blade 3<br>
18 - Raging Flurry 3<br>
<br>
Yes, I do consider Rampage and all that increase Riposte stuff such a waste of effort that im not ever gonna bother.<br>
<br>
Finally, if the sun hasn't burned out yet:<br>
3 - First Aid 3<br>
3 - Improved Natural Regeneration 3<br>
12 - Natural Healing 3<br>
18 - Bandage Wounds 3<br>
9 - Mithaniel's Binding 2<br>
<br>
Total: 263 <br>
